{{italic title}}
The '''''Canadian Guide to Uniform Legal Citation''''' (a.k.a. the '''''McGill Guide'''''), establishes the [[legal citation]] standard in [[Canada]]. It is published by the ''[[McGill Law Journal]]'' of the [[McGill University Faculty of Law]] and is used by law students and [[lawyer]]s throughout Canada. The book is [[bilingual]], one half being in [[English language|English]] and the other in [[French language|French]] (''Manuel canadien de la référence juridique''). Its 8th edition was published in 2014.

