== Operating system support ==
The [[operating system]]s the daemons can run on without emulation; also supported I/O facilities for network sockets (see [[IRCd]] for further information).
{| class="wikitable sortable" style="font-size: 85%; text-align: center;"
|-
! IRC daemon
! [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]
! [[DOS]]
! [[Mac OS]]
! [[Linux]]
! [[BSD]]
! [[Solaris (operating system)|Solaris]]
! [[HP-UX]]
! [[IBM AIX|AIX]]

! [[Select (Unix)|select()]]
! poll()
! [[epoll]]<ref name="epoll">[http://www.xmailserver.org/linux-patches/nio-improve.html epoll]. xmailserver.org. ([[Linux]] since 2.6) - I/O event notification facility. Has a much better performance than [[Select (Unix)|select()]] and poll() system calls.</ref>
! [[kqueue]]<ref name="kqueue">kqueue ([[FreeBSD]] since 4.1) - asynchronous event dispatch mechanism.</ref>
! [[Thread (computing)|threads]]
! RT signals<ref name="rtsigio">"[[POSIX]].4 Real Time Signals" ([[Linux]] since 2.4) - special class of Linux system signals used for notification of events on file descriptors. Deprecated in favour of [http://www.xmailserver.org/linux-patches/nio-improve.html epoll].</ref>
! /dev/poll<ref>{{cite web|url=http://access1.sun.com/techarticles/devpoll.html |title=Using the devpoll (/dev/poll) Interface |first=Shridhar |last=Acharya |date=March 2002 |publisher=Sun.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070202231908/http://access1.sun.com/techarticles/devpoll.html |archivedate=February 2, 2007 |deadurl=unfit }}</ref>
! Windows IOCP<ref>[http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa363862.aspx "CreateIoCompletionPort function"]. Microsoft MSDN Library.</ref>
! Solaris IOCP<ref>[http://developers.sun.com/solaris/articles/event_completion.html "The Event Completion Framework for the Solaris Operating System (Solaris IOCP)"]. Sun.com.</ref>
|-

