{{self-published|date=February 2016}} '''''Gazetteer of the Bombay Presidency''''' is a publication of the erstwhile British India first published in the year 1894 and printed at the Government Central Press, [[Bombay]] (now [[Mumbai]]) in 1896. Since the early 19th Century the [[English East India Company]] and later the [[British Empire]] annexed most of Western India and collectively named the provinces in Western India as [[Bombay Presidency]].
Most of these texts are now available free to read online as scanned books (see External Links).
Each volume in the publications consists of the historic, geographic and demographic information of the numerous British and princely states under the presidency. The general editor of the first edition was [[James Macnabb Campbell]].<ref>{{cite ODNB|id=32266|first=Peter|last=Harnetty|title=Campbell, Sir James Macnabb}}</ref>
==Volumes==
===Part I=== Part I consists of * History of Gujarat * History of other minor states - Sholapur, Belgaum, etc.
===Part II=== Part II consists of five books, namely;
* Book I - History of The [[Konkan]], By The Reverend Alexander Kyd Nairne.<ref name="asianeds">{{cite web|url=http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=416&BC=b|title=History of the Konkan|publisher=web.archive.org|accessdate=2015-11-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309060904/http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=416&BC=b|archivedate=2012-03-09|df=}}</ref> * Book II - Early History Of The [[Deccan Plateau|Dakhan]] down to the Mahomedan Conquest, By Professor [[Ramkrishna Gopal Bhandarkar]]<ref name="asianeds2">{{cite web|url=http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=955&BC=b|title=Early History of the Dekkan|publisher=web.archive.org|accessdate=2015-11-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309060908/http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=955&BC=b|archivedate=2012-03-09|df=}}</ref> * Book III - The Dynasties of the [[Kanarese]] Districts of The [[Bombay Presidency]] from the earliest historical times to the Musalman Conquest, By [[John Faithfull Fleet]]<ref name="asianeds3">{{cite web|url=http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=194&BC=b|title=Dynasties of the Kanarese Districts of the Bombay Presidency|publisher=web.archive.org|accessdate=2015-11-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309060913/http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=194&BC=b|archivedate=2012-03-09|df=}}</ref> * Book IV - Dakhan History, Musalman and [[Maratha]], AD 1300–1818, Part I-[[Poona]] [[History of Satara district|Satara]] and [[Sholapur]], Part II-[[Khandesh]] [[Nashik]] and [[Ahmadnagar]], By W.W.Loch<ref name="asianeds4">{{cite web|url=http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=351&BC=b|title=Dakhan History Musalman and Maratha (AD 1300-1818)|publisher=web.archive.org|accessdate=2015-11-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309060928/http://asianeds.com/book_cd_details.asp?Cd=351&BC=b|archivedate=2012-03-09|df=}}</ref> * Book V - History of the [[Bombay]] [[Karnataka]], Musalman and Maratha, A.D 1300–1818, Colonel E.W.West
== References == {{Reflist}}
==External links== *{{cite book|title=The Dynasties of the Kanarese Districts of the Bombay Presidency from the Earliest Historical Times to the Musalman Conquest of A.D. 1318|author=Fleet, J.F.|date=1988|publisher=Asian Educational Services|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=yOC1AAAAIAAJ|accessdate=2015-11-13}} * {{cite book |title=Gazetteer of the Bombay Presidency (Volume XXI)|author= |publisher=Government Central Press|year=1884|isbn= |page= |url=https://archive.org/stream/gazetteerbombay23enthgoog#page/n6/mode/2up |ref= }} *{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=0bkMAAAAIAAJ|title=Gazetteer of the Bombay Presidency ... – Books on Google Play|publisher=play.google.com|accessdate=2015-11-13}} *{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/search?q=gazzetteer+of+the+Bombay+presidency&c=books|title=gazzetteer of the Bombay presidency – Books on Google Play|publisher=play.google.com|accessdate=2015-11-13}}
