{{Infobox Museum |name = Martyrs' Memorial |image = File:Amman martyr's memorial.jpg |imagesize = |caption = Martyrs' Memorial entrance |alt = |map_type = |map_caption = |map_alt = |coordinates = {{coord|31.98655|35.90640|format=dms|type:landmark_region:JO|display=inline,title}} |established = 1977 |dissolved = |location = [[Amman]], [[Jordan]] |type = [[Memorial]] |visitors = |director = |curator = |publictransit = |website = }}
'''Martyrs' Memorial''' is a memorial and museum in [[Amman]], [[Jordan]]. Located next to the Amman Sport city, the museum was established in 1977 upon [[King Hussein of Jordan|King Hussein]]'s wishes. The museum showcases a rare collection of Jordan's military weapons, clothing and vehicles. It also serves as a memorial to the martyrs who gave their lives in the service of Jordan as early as 1915, starting with the [[Arab Revolt|Great Arab Revolution]] which was led by King Hussein's grandfather [[Hussein bin Ali, Sharif of Mecca|Hussein bin Ali]].<ref>{{cite web|title=MUSEUM – The Martyrs’ Memorial and Museum, Jordan|url=http://www.military-history.org/articles/museum-the-martyrs-memorial-and-museum-jordan.htm|website=Military History Monthly|accessdate=30 December 2016|date=18 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A Tour to Jordan|url=http://www.jewishmag.com/133mag/jordan/jordan.htm|website=www.jewishmag.com|accessdate=30 December 2016}}</ref>
